com.eyetechds.quicklink

Class QLSettings

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.eyetechds.quicklink.QLSettings

  • public class QLSettings
extends java.lang.Object
    A QLSettings object is a container for holding settings used by QLDevice objects. The settings container can be filled with settings two different ways. It can be filled manually or by loading from a file.

    Manually adding settings
    There are two methods that can be used to manually fill a settings container with settings. A setting can be added without an initial value by calling add(String). A setting can be added with an initial value by calling setValue(String, String). It is not necessary to call add(String) and then call setValue(String, String). Calling setValue(String, String) will add a setting to the container if it does not already exist.

    Loading from a file
    Settings can be loaded from a file by using the method load(FileChannel). If the data in the file is valid then the settings object will contain the settings and values after loading.

    Importing and exporting
    Devices can import and export settings by calling QLDevice.importSettings(QLSettings) or QLDevice.exportSettings(QLSettings). The device will only import or export settings that are already contained in the settings object. It will not add additional settings to the container. It is up to the developer to populate the settings object with the desired settings before importing or exporting.

    See Also:
    QLDevice

      • DEVICE_DOWNSAMPLE_SCALE_FACTOR

        public static final java.lang.String DEVICE_DOWNSAMPLE_SCALE_FACTOR
        The setting name for the downsample scale factor of the image. A value of 1.0 will send the full size image. A value less than 1.0 will not send any image. A value greater than 1.0 will scale the image by that amount in both the x and y direction before sending it to the host.

        Using this setting properly will help reduce bandwidth needs and system resources. If an image is not being displayed then it is recommended that the downsample scale factor be set to zero so that no image data is sent. It is also recommended that this setting be used to pre-downsample the image to the size of the display area where the image is to be drawn. This can save on system resources while displaying the image.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • load

        public int load(java.nio.channels.FileChannel fileChannel)
         throws java.io.IOException
        Load settings from a file channel. The settings are read from the current position of the file channel until the end of the file channel. The position of the file channel is incremented by the number of bytes read.
        Parameters:
        fileChannel - A FileChannel from which the settings will be loaded.

        Returns:
        The number of bytes read from the file channel.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Signals that an I/O exception has occurred.
        See Also:
        save(FileChannel), FileChannel

      • save

        public int save(java.nio.channels.FileChannel fileChannel)
         throws java.io.IOException
        Save the settings to a file channel. The settings can later be loaded by calling load(FileChannel). The contents of the file channel are overwritten starting at the current position of the file channel. The position of the file channel is incremented by the number of bytes written.
        Parameters:
        fileChannel - A FileChannel to which the settings will be saved.

        Returns:
        The number of bytes written to the file channel.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Signals that an I/O exception has occurred.
        See Also:
        load(FileChannel), FileChannel
